# Read and Rise Website Build Spec (for Cursor / 5.2-codex)

## 0) Project Overview
- Org: Read and Rise
- Relationship: Read and Rise is a sister organization to OneProsper International (not “formerly”).
- Primary outcomes:
  1) Donations / fundraising (Donately)
  2) Buddy signups (USA/Canada high school girls)
  3) School-admin signups (USA/Canada high school administrators)
- Homepage is a single long-scroll page with a Students/Schools toggle that refreshes segment content below the toggle.
- Primary CTA is fixed: “Join read & rise”.

## 1) Site Map
- / (Home: single long-scroll with Students/Schools toggle)
- /about (Leadership Team, Directors & Advisors, History, Sister-org relationship to OneProsper)
- /donate (Donately embed or donate redirect)
- /signup (email capture + selector modal + redirect to Google Form)
- /privacy-policy
- /terms-of-service

## 2) Component Inventory (with copy requirements)
Global
- StickyNav: logo + links (About, Donate, Sign Up), Donate and Sign Up styled as CTAs.
- Donate CTA appears in: StickyNav + Hero + Donate section + Footer.

Homepage Sections (shared structure; segment-specific content)
- Hero: 2-column (LHS copy + CTAs, RHS image)
- AudienceToggle: Students (default) / Schools (on toggle, refresh content sections below)
- Section 3.1 Challenge: 3 cards, each requires an image
- Section 3.2 Solution: 3 cards, each requires an image
- Section 3.3 Stats: 3 separate stat boxes (not inline text)
- Section 3.4 Logos: row of 6 school logos
- Section 3.5 Buddy testimonials: carousel; each item has text + image/video
- Section 3.6 Learner testimonials: carousel; each item has text + image/video
- Section 3.7 School admin testimonials: carousel; each item has text + image/video; ONLY this content type
- Section 3.8 How it works: new dedicated section; 6 steps with icons
- Section 3.9 Benefits: 3 cards, each requires an image
- Section 3.10 Join Us: email capture + on click open modal selector (Student / School Admin) + redirect to appropriate Google Form URL
- Section 3.11 Donate: “Sponsor a learner” framing; Donately embed/redirect

Footer
- Sister-org line repeated
- Social links, About links (Leadership Team, Directors & Advisors, History), Privacy Policy, Terms, Donate CTA

